cc:Work.dc:title: The Open Group Architecture Framework (TOGAF)
cc:Work.dc:description:
A framework for Enterprise Architecture which provides a comprehensive approach to the design, planning, implementation, and governance of an enterprise information architecture. The architecture is typically modeled at four levels or domains; Business, Application, Data, Technology.
A set of foundation architectures are provided to enable the architecture team to envision the current and future state of the architecture.
